Genitalia. Surstyli asymmetrical, OS with a pointed tip in dorsal view; epandrium elongated; m.a. as wide as 1/3 of ST8 (
Fig. 28G
). SES with hairy ridges on both sides; gonopods short, both with medial lobes (overlapping in ventral view, 
